 * Add `getInstance()` methods to ensure only one instance of the driver in an app and make constructor private
 * Tidy up demo app
 * Update build tools

```java
    Mididriver midi = MidiDriver.getInstance();
    // or
    Mididriver midi = MidiDriver.getInstance(this);  // Add listener
    // or
    Mididriver midi = MidiDriver.getInstance(() ->  // Use lambda expression
        // Do whatever
        );
```

![ic_launcher](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3448386/70924065-d69ee000-2020-11ea-9f24-980c36efc6b0.png)
 * Add setReverb by @b3b 
 * Update build tools
```java
    boolean setReverb(int preset) // Set Reverb effect preset for EAS
                                  // synthesizer (value from
                                  // ReverbConstants). Returns true
                                  // on success, false on failure
```

![ic_launcher](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3448386/44095939-ee219202-9fd1-11e8-99f0-c62bef7cfa54.png)
* Remove armeabi, mips, mips64
* Remove arm assembler, GNU as no longer supported
* Add C/C++ native interface
```C++
#include "midi.h"

    jboolean midi_init()  // Return true on success, or false on failure.
    jboolean midi_write(EAS_U8 *bytes, jint length)
                                 // Writes midi data to the Sonivox
                                 // synthesizer. The length of the array
                                 // should be the exact length of the
                                 // message or messages. Returns true
                                 // on success, false on
                                 // failure.
    jboolean midi_setVolume(jint volume)
                                  // Set master volume for EAS
                                  // synthesizer (between 0 and 100).
                                  // Returns true on success, false on
                                  // failure.
    jboolean midi_shutdown() // Shut down the synthesizer. Returns true on
                             // success, false on failure.
```
